## USER RESEARCH

**Where the audience actually talks:** Quora threads on gel vs extensions for short nails, TikTok DIY nail communities, Lemon8 natural nail growth communities, Facebook groups (DIY Nails at Home, I Love Your Nails), SalonGeek forums, YouTube tutorial comment sections, Amazon review sections for nail tip products.

### Top 5 Pain Points

1. **"Are my nails even long enough?"** — Users don't know the minimum length required for the almond taper. Many quit before trying because they assume short means impossible.
2. **"I end up with oval, not almond"** — The most common shaping error. People file too little from the sides, rounding the tip instead of tapering it. The almond-vs-oval confusion is everywhere.
3. **"One nail ends up pointier than the others"** — Asymmetry frustration. Filing freehand without a guide leads to inconsistent results across fingers.
4. **"My tip just collapses when I file"** — Users with very short nails lose too much structure when tapering, ending up with nothing left. They don't know about the centre-mark trick or the tip-addition option.
5. **"I don't want extensions but I also don't have the length"** — The in-between problem. Users don't know press-ons or gel tips exist as a middle-ground DIY option. They think the only alternatives are grow-or-salon.

**User Sentiment:** Determined but anxious — they want to do this themselves and are willing to learn, but they're scared of ruining what length they have.

